Cobham plc Logo
Cobham Limited is a British manufacturing company based in Wimborne Minster, England. Cobham was originally founded by Sir Alan Cobham as Flight Refuelling Limited in 1934. During 1939, British airline Imperial Airways performed several non-stop crossings of the Atlantic using equipment provided by FRL. During the late 1940s, the company’s aerial refuelling equipment broke new ground, including a round-the-world flight by specially-equipped Boeing B-50 Superfortresses in 1948 and the demonstration of the now-widely used ‘probe and drogue’ method of air-to-air refuelling for the first time in 1949.
